<subSubSection box="[199,1180,369,395]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="101.[151,1437,153,575]" box="[199,1180,369,395]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,369,395]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Etymology.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[391,439,369,395]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
locality is latinised thus Tioman to tiomana, a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="101.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,405,431]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Remarks.</emphasis>
The similarly coloured 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic 1914" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1914" box="[584,909,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notaticollis">
<emphasis box="[584,803,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Luciola notaticollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pic" box="[810,909,405,431]" firstAuthor="Pic" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="3" refId="ref121203" refString="Pic, M. (1914) Nouveau genre, especes et varietes nouvelles de diverses familles. Melanges exotico-Entomologiques, 10, 3." type="journal article" year="1914">Pic 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Madura 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1130,405,431]" name="India" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">India</collectingCountry>
is 7.0 mm long, with black pronotum, MN, and MS, and the basal area of the elytra (slightly less than half the length) orange, with the apical ½ of the elytron black. The 
<typeStatus box="[506,554,477,503]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
in MNHN was examined but not dissected as it is glued face down on a card. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne &amp; Jusoh" box="[151,456,513,540]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref114336" refString="Ballantyne, L. A &amp; Jusoh, W. F. A. (2016) List of genera and species in the Luciolinae from SE Asia and the Australopacific Version 2. Checklist of IndoPacific Luciolinae, 2016, 1 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.13140 / RG. 2.1.4635.2241" type="journal article" year="2016">Ballantyne &amp; Jusoh (2016)</bibRefCitation>
suggested a closer examination was necessary to determine if 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1914" box="[1164,1320,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notaticollis">
<emphasis box="[1164,1320,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">L. notaticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[283,359,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Curtos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,359,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Curtos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
